definition: gate/door/CL:扇[shan4]/gateway/doorway/CL:個|个[ge4]/opening/valve/switch/way to do something/knack/family/house/(religious) sect/school (of thought)/class/category/phylum or division (taxonomy)/classifier for large guns/classifier for lessons, subjects, branches of technology/(suffix) -gate (i.e. scandal; derived from Watergate)

sentences.english: Hyperechoic incisor teeth can be seen in the opened mouth.
sentences.chinese: 可以看到張開的口中的強回聲的門齒。

sentences.english: Rodents are small mammals with large front teeth.
sentences.chinese: 齧齒目動物是長着大門齒的小哺乳動物。

sentences.english: Flared incisors and deep overbite are challenging to treat orthodontically.
sentences.chinese: 爆發門齒和深覆具有挑戰性治療正畸。

sentences.english: A pair of upper and lower jaw have sharp incisors.
sentences.chinese: 上下顎各有一對銳利的門齒。

sentences.english: As for patients with missing 3 lower incisors, space was preserved for prosthodontic reconstruction.
sentences.chinese: 缺失3顆下顎門齒者則留下假牙贗復的空間。
